nodes.text: It seems for some, the birth canal somehow magically transforms the unborn into a person. One minute it's not a person, the next, it is!

Really. For that reason, we, antiabortion atheists, hold that abortionist are really religious nuts who believe that a soul exists and penetrates into a body along with the first air breathing. Chester:
Among other things, the newborn must obtain its own oxygen and its own nourishment. It must also transition from an aquatic environment to an aerobic one.
So, if a baby is having trouble breathing that's been born already, you don't consider it a 'person'? Methinks you've not thought through the implications of your argument here at all.
